<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Updates&nbsp;on&nbsp;Project&nbsp;Farii</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">Showing&nbsp;updates...</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<div class="material-box" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
<p>A meta-analysis conducted by the Memetic and Infohazards Division showed that subjects from younger demographics had lower rates of fatality compared to to the average.</p>
<p>Cross-referencing with historical data revealed that individuals between the ages of 7 - 16 are at their most flexible in terms of memetic processing, and would be significantly more suited for Project Farii - predicting a drop in the fatality rate to 12%.</p>
<div class="blockquote">
<p>In order to perform its duty, the Foundation must be at the forefront in every field, anomalous ones included. To that end, it is of utmost importance that the Foundation establish a process of imparting knowledge free from the constraints of experience or time.</p>
<p>The supply of subjects within the suitable age range will be handled by Logistics and Human Resources. With these conditions, we hereby authorize the continuation of Project Farii.</p>
<p>We'll be expecting good results, Desigr. Crowsworth.</p>
<div style="text-align: right;">
<p><strong>- O5 Council</strong></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;</span></p>
<div class="material-box" style="margin-bottom: 16px;">
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p><strong><tt><span style="font-size:125%;">Amendments to PROJECT FARII</span></tt></strong></p>
</div>
<hr />
<p>In conjunction with new adaptations of the Foundation Ascension Program, Project Farii has been modified to contain three additional steps:</p>
<ul>
<li>Candidates of Foundation Ascension Program will undergo intensive amnestics treatment, serving twofold purposes: maximizing available memory capacity, and standardizing subjects' condition in preparation for the implant stage.</li>
<li>Undesirable personality traits are to be overwritten using modified outputs of <em>Project Aletheia</em> to minimize chances of implant failure, as well as increasing potential productivity level upon the completion of the program.</li>
<li>In the events of difficulty when establishing false history and memory under Foundation employment, <em>Project Kallinikos</em> is to be deployed, pending O5 approval.</li>
</ul>
<hr />
<p>It is expected that with the success of Farii, Foundation workforce will have a substantial increase of up to 1000 new high-skill employees a year.<br /></p>
<div style="text-align: center;">
<p>The future of the Foundation will be secured.</p>
</div>
